parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warped front brake rotors can cause the steering wheel to vibrate or shake violently when braking, especially at high speeds, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.

the vehicle shakes or vibrates when slowing down
and the brakes feel soft or spongy.
